5:
A man who was looking for Rhode
and Vriki, you say?
8:
Yeah. A work associate of her dad's,
by the sound of it. He said he wants
to tell Rhode exactly what happened.
11:
I can't help but find the whole thing
rather suspicious. Why has this man
appeared now, of all times?
16:
I agree... But if it means Rhode can
get closure about her father...
19:
It might be worth meeting this guy. I
figure I'll go and see him by myself. I
do have a favor to ask you, though.
24:
I'm sorry. I don't think I can let you
meet Rhode after all.
26:
If you have something to tell her,
you can relay the message through
me.
29:
Hahaha. Come now, no need to be
like that. I'd very much like to speak
with her directly. Would you kindly
oblige me?
31:
I'm afraid that's not possible. I have
nothing else to say to you, so—
34:
That's all right. I guess I'll have the
rest of this conversation with Rhode
herself. Lucky for me, she's right here.
45:
Let's continue this conversation
somewhere a little more private.
50:
I'm surprised to see that you didn't
take that walking diving suit along
with you. What did you call him?
Vriki?
53:
I left him behind because I knew Alk
would get suspicious...
56:
If you so much as lay a hand on her,
Vriki will make you regret it. He'll
come rushing to save her.
59:
That's precisely what I'm counting
on.
63: Stop it! Don't you dare hurt her!
66:
My, my... That was faster than I
expected.
83:
This barrier was designed to contain
dragons, you know. Good to know
that even a follower of the Devourer
of Stars cannot break its hold.
85:
With this, I am one step closer to my
goal... To throw off these mortal
shackles... To transcend humanity!
89: Break free, Vriki! Don't give up! Dad!
92:
Heh. Let me give you a closer look at
this thing you call your father.
96: Stop! She doesn't need to see that!
118:
Impossible! A follower of the
Devourer of Stars possesses the
ability of human speech? Or is it
merely due to the consciousness
that it absorbed...
126:
I'm sorry... You were just trying to
protect Rhode this whole time.
136:
Sorry I'm late. Let's get out of here,
Rhode.
139:
The Devourer of Stars is already
within my grasp! I have no further
need of you—
142:
Vriki... He was just acting as your
protector, Rhode.
145:
He may not be your real father, but...
he cares for you.
147:
Can you accept him for what he is,
Rhode?
151:
I... was so alone. I missed my dad so
much.
153:
But even if you're not actually my
dad...
160: I'm sorry. I'm so, so sorry.
166: I... I still want to be with you! Forever!
204:
The great hero Verikion doesn't hurt
the weak and helpless.
207: So just toss that man aside.
223:
That's right, having a wash does
brighten the mood!
227:
Oh come on, don't pretend you
understand him. All he does is make
weird, low whirring noises.
231:
I was just going off feeling, you
know? I have no idea what he
actually said.
235:
You two have to listen more
carefully to what he says! He can
speak.
239:
Vriki and I are going shopping today,
so he wants to look his best. Isn't
that right?
253:
Nope. Still just sounds like a broken
refrigerator to me.
